text: Vicki Wysocki is an American scientist. She is a professor at Ohio State University.Ohio State Profile She received a BS in Chemistry from Western Kentucky University in 1982 and her PhD in Chemistry at Purdue University in 1987. She was the president of the American Society for Mass Spectrometry for the period of 2016-2018https://www.asms.org/about/asms-leadership/past- presidents and has received the Field and Franklin Award in 2017https://www.acs.org/content/acs/en/funding-and- awards/awards/national/bytopic/frank-h-field-and-joe-l-franklin-award-for- outstanding-achievement-in-mass-spectrometry.html. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Purdue University alumni Category:Living people Category:Chemists Category:Mass spectrometrists Category:Ohio State University faculty Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
